PEOPLE 
Carter Hawley Hale Stores Inc. has named Gregory C. Crews, president of the 
Weinstocks division, to the additional post of chief executive. Crews succeeds 
Cheryl Nido Turpin, who is leaving the company after a successful career at 
both The Broadway-Southern California and Weinstocks, which is in Sacramento. 
The chairman's position at the division will not be filled. Crews was named 
president in September after having served as president and chief executive of 
Carter Hawley Hale's Market Services division since 1985. 
